p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    10\cdot\left( -{\frac{9}{2}} \right)
    \amp =\frac{10}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{9}{2}}\right) \amp \hbox{We can divide both the first numerator and the second denominator by 2.}\\
    \amp =\frac{5}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{9}{1}}\right)\\
    \amp ={-45}
    \end{aligned}}
